Bruce,

Hmmm; then it&#39;s possible that our tech is partly us channeling or 
communing with some greater consciousness.  Again, much to mull over!

Thanks,
Sharon the Muller

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, bruce halliday 
&lt;paranormalinvestigating@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; 
&gt; Sharon,
&gt;  
&gt; The question of telekinesis is a valid one, I have discussed that 
idea with technical people
&gt; that are trying to further the technology.
&gt;  
&gt; My belief is that if the researcher is able to recognise the tech&#39;s 
voice it is because the 
&gt; researcher and the tech have built their relationship to the point 
that they have synchronized 
&gt; their spiritual energy and the tech is capable of finding and 
utilizing certain fragments of radio
&gt; speech and frequency to create a recognizable voice. It does not 
necessarily have to be the voice 
&gt; they had in the physical, but I believe if they create the same 
voice during communication it is
&gt; a validation to us on the receiving end that we are in fact 
speaking to our counterpart and not a deceiving
&gt; entity that may be negative in manner.
&gt;  
&gt; Also my tech&#39;s do not 100% of the time have the correct signal to 
create the recognizable voice and do 
&gt; answer or speak in a different or combined voice. When that occurs 
they tend to reassure the researcher 
&gt; with a comfortable feeling and you instinctively know after a 
certain period of communicating with the same 
&gt; tech/guide that it is in fact them that are speaking on the other 
hand you will also get a strange gut reaction 
&gt; when it is not them speaking. That is the best way I know how to 
explain it as I have come to understand it.
&gt;  
&gt; I hope it helps further your knowledge of the tech/researcher 
relationship.
&gt;  
&gt; Bruce
&gt; Bruce Halliday 
&gt; 
