for a masculine fragment or signal&gt; &gt; and lisa will wait for a 
feminine one. I believe they try to answer &gt; in the apropriate gender 
so that I &gt; &gt; don&#39;t get confused about who is answering. Sometimes I 
will get a &gt; response or message that is made &gt; &gt; up of both male and 
female voices together, even in the same word &gt; sometimes but very 
rarely.&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; And I think when that occurs it&#39;s because they lose 
the particular &gt; fragment midstream and pick up &gt; &gt; whatever is 
available at that instant to complete the message , &gt; word or 
phrase.&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; I hope this answers your question and please keep 
asking them. It &gt; forces me to formulate an answer&gt; &gt; and you to 
